cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.CC 

The paper deals with decoding algorithms for linear block codes, which are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT). The use of Integer Programming (IP) and Linear Programming (LP) also suggests a connection to optimization and algorithms (cs.DS, cs.DC). The paper also proposes a new formulation and algorithm for finding violated parity checks, which could be relevant to machine learning and pattern recognition (cs.LG). Finally, the use of LDPC codes and BCH codes suggests a connection to coding theory and error correction (cs.CC).
